title: Google\Cloud\Compute\V1\SerialPortOutput
name: SerialPortOutput
description:
An instance's serial console output.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.compute.v1.SerialPortOutput

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.contents
params.description: [Output Only] The contents of the console output.

params.name: data.kind
params.description: [Output Only] Type of the resource. Always compute#serialPortOutput for serial port output.

params.name: data.next
params.description: [Output Only] The position of the next byte of content, regardless of whether the content exists, following the output returned in the contents property. Use this value in the next request as the start parameter.

params.name: data.self_link
params.description: [Output Only] Server-defined URL for this resource.

params.name: data.start
params.description: The starting byte position of the output that was returned. This should match the start parameter sent with the request. If the serial console output exceeds the size of the buffer (1 MB), older output is overwritten by newer content. The output start value will indicate the byte position of the output that was returned, which might be different than the start value that was specified in the request.
